{
  "text": "Consequently, we can regard the model of the prey-predator population dynamics given by (16) as a time-discrete version corresponding to the LotkaVolterra prey-predator model [CITATION_1] . Further, we could regard the prey-predator reaction term given by a rational function in (16) as a temporally integrated (over the period of the discrete time step) mass-action type of prey-predator reaction, because of the correspondence with the mass-action term in the ODE model (8).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "117771948"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "117771948": {
      "title": "Discrete competitive and cooperative models of Lotka-Volterra type",
      "abstract": "The dynamics of discrete Lotka\u2013Volterra system of two species is investigated. It is shown that the proposed discrete models for competitive and cooperative systems possess \u201cdynamical consistency\u201d with their continuous counterparts."
    }
  }
}